After listening to Senator Dianne Feinstein question Neil Gorsuch during the latest round of the judge’s confirmation hearing, Lindsey Graham had had enough. 
The Republican senator from South Carolina responded to the California Democrat’s repeated attempt to “uncover evidence” of Gorsuch’s conservative views on originalism, torture, and on other issues, Graham responded with a mini-rant that accused the Democrats and others in her party of ‘looking for someone who would make their political lives easier which they were not going to get from Trump.’ 
