Graham criticized the apparent “double standard” by Democrats between nominees chosen by a Democratic president versus a Republican president, pointing out that he voted for former President Barack Obama’s two nominees, Justices Sonia Sotomayor and Elena Kagan, because they were qualified, not because they would advance his preferred agenda. “What more can you ask for?” Graham asked his Democratic peers  1464204305408-0'); }); 
